<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: MOORPARK; 
</P>
<P>
EX-BANK MANAGER INDICTED IN FRAUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURA PITTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former assistant vice president and manager of the Moorpark branch of Simi 
Valley Bank was indicted Wednesday on federal bank fraud and embezzlement 
charges. 
</P>
<P>
Frank John Szabo, 33, is accused of falsifying documents to obtain a $21,000 
loan to buy a Mercedes-Benz, FBI spokesman Gary Auer said. 
</P>
<P>
Szabo allegedly applied for a personal loan but used the name of an individual 
not connected to the transaction. Loan documents also contained fictitious 
credit and tax information, Auer said. 
</P>
<P>
Szabo is scheduled to be arraigned in federal court in Los Angeles on Monday. 
LAURA PITTER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080990-0009 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 258963 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 9, 1990, Thursday, Ventura County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
