<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TALK-SHOW HOST NAMED TO COMMUNICATIONS POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Truman Jacques, a talk-show host on KCBS, has been named Inglewood's director 
of communications, a new position created to improve the government's image and 
its communications with residents. 
</P>
<P>
Jacques, who will begin work Aug. 27, has been manager of public communications 
for the Southern California Assn. of Governments for the past four years and an 
associate producer and host on KCBS for the past 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
"We are fortunate to have attracted a man with Mr. Jacques' tremendous 
background and depth of experience," said City Manager Paul D. Eckles. "I'm 
confident he will be able to expand and improve our efforts to communicate 
effectively with our residents." 
</P>
</TEXT>
