<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANGING THE ENDANGERED SPECIES ACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commentary was correct in that we are endangering the human race; not, 
however, for the reasons stated. 
</P>
<P>
While it is true that the preservation of wildlife means the loss of jobs, 
these same jobs are endangered by limited resources. 
</P>
<P>
The extinction of any species, even one as seemingly inconsequential as the 
snail darter, has drastic effects on the area it habitats. In short, it causes 
a chain reaction which upsets the natural balance of things. In the long run, 
this hurts the human race much more than a higher unemployment rate could. 
