<P>
SmithKline Beecham: The Anglo-American health and household products company 
reported that its second-quarter profit was $303 million, 47% higher than the 
same quarter of 1989. 
</P>
<P>
The London-based company said the good performance was highlighted by continued 
sales growth, strong operating profit and significant debt reduction. Sales 
were up 3% to $2.1 billion. The results are the second set reported on a 
quarterly basis since Beecham PLC and SmithKline Beckman Corp. merged in July, 
1989. Year-earlier figures are presented as if the merger had been in place in 
the second quarter of 1989. 
