<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE ORIGINS OF 'GET A LIFE!' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re "Get a Life!" (July 26): I enjoyed Nikki Finke's article very much, but the 
statement "Get a life!" has been around a lot longer than she may realize. 
Perhaps a sketch on "Saturday Night Live" helped popularize the expression, but 
my ex-girlfriend's best friend used to say it frequently in 1979, with the same 
intent it has today. 
</P>
<P>
If she read the piece and some of the dates presented therein for this phrase's 
possible origins (1986, 1988) . . . well, you know what she would have said. 
</P>
<P>
MIKE HARRINGTON 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 
</P>
