<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOODLAND HILLS TEAM BEATEN IN U.S. OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Woodland Hills Astros surrendered two runs in the bottom of the ninth 
inning and fell to the Florida Braves, 3-2, Tuesday night in a National 
Division game of the U.S. Open Baseball tournament at Galvin Field in Ontario. 
</P>
<P>
The Astros, 3-1 in the tournament, complete division play tonight against the 
Fairbanks (Alaska) Goldpanners (4-0). 
</P>
<P>
First- and second-place finishers in the National and American divisions 
advance to another tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Against the Braves, the Astros scored in the second inning on a single by Rio 
Mesa High senior-to-be Dmitri Young, then in the third on a two-out double by 
Billy Morris. 
</P>
