<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: 3 NIGHT HOME FOOTBALL GAMES ON MOORPARK COLLEGE SCHEDULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moorpark College will play home football games at night for the first time this 
season, scheduling three of its five games on campus for 7:30 p.m. The Raiders' 
night games will be against Valley (Sept. 22), Santa Barbara (Nov. 3) and 
Ventura (Nov. 17). The games against L. A. Southwest (Oct. 6) and Compton (Oct. 
20) are scheduled for 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Podley, a former player at Notre Dame High, has been named the football 
coach at Northview High in Covina. 
</P>
<P>
Podley, 31, formerly worked as an assistant coach at Notre Dame (for two 
years), Servite (two years) and Mater Dei (four years). Last season, he served 
as the offensive coordinator for Muir Coach John Tyree. Muir shared the 
Southern Section Division II title with Santa Barbara in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Podley succeeds Kevin Gair, who directed Northview to a 4-7 record last fall. 
</P>
