<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
</P>
<P>
NEW AUTO DEALERSHIP OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved an agreement with a Montclair car dealer to put a 
new Jeep-Eagle auto dealership in the Pomona Auto Center, along the Corona 
Expressway. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for the redevelopment agency to sell the 3.3-acre site for 
$445,776 to Pomona Valley Jeep-Eagle Inc., which has been formed by the owner 
of Pomona Valley Dodge in Montclair. 
</P>
<P>
The redevelopment agency will give the dealer $400,000 in sales tax rebates if 
the dealership meets certain conditions, including opening within a year after 
the close of escrow. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas B. Dunlap, deputy executive director of the redevelopment agency, said 
the owners plan to open the dealership in eight months and expect to generate 
$20 million in sales the first year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
