<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
10% WATER CUTBACK URGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern California's continuing drought prompted the City Council to adopt a 
resolution asking residents to curtail water use by 10% compared with last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
The council also urged restaurants to serve water to patrons only when asked. 
</P>
<P>
South Pasadena belongs to the Upper San Gabriel Valley Municipal Water 
District, which has urged its members to adopt water-saving policies. If 
voluntary measures don't achieve the 10% reduction, the city may consider 
enacting a mandatory water conservation program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
