<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONROVIA; 
</P>
<P>
CITY SCORES WELL ON SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine of 10 residents think that city services are adequate or better, and one 
out of four could not name a single thing that they disliked about living in 
the city, according to a recent telephone survey commissioned by the City 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
The survey sampled 409 Monrovia residents from every corner of the city and 
every ethnic background. 
</P>
<P>
The qualities most people listed when asked what they liked about living in 
Monrovia were the small-town community feeling, the city's redevelopment 
efforts and proximity to other areas. When they found something to dislike, 
residents cited smog, hillside development and drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
