<P>
PRESIDING JUDGE NOMINATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A state appellate court judge from Culver City has been nominated to serve as 
presiding justice for the 2nd District Court of Appeal, Division 5. 
</P>
<P>
Paul A. Turner, an associate justice for the 2nd District court, was nominated 
to the post Monday by Gov. George Deukmejian. 
</P>
<P>
On the appellate court since last fall, he would replace Campbell Lucas, who 
plans to retire at the end of the year. 
</P>
<P>
The nomination requires approval by a state judicial commission. 
</P>
<P>
Turner, 42, worked in private law firms before being appointed a Los Angeles 
Municipal Court judge by Deukmejian in 1983. He was named a Superior Court 
judge two years later. 
</P>
<P>
He graduated from Cal State Long Beach in 1969 and UCLA Law School in 1972. 
</P>
</TEXT>
