WESTSIDE DIGEST: LOS ANGELES; 
</P>
<P>
FEINSTEIN PICKS COUNCILMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Democratic gubernatorial nominee Dianne Feinstein has named Los Angeles City 
Councilman Michael Woo to head her Southern California advisory committee on 
Asian and Pacific-Americans. 
</P>
<P>
Feinstein announced the appointment during a campaign stop in Los Angeles on 
Tuesday. The committee, composed of community and business leaders from various 
Asian and Pacific communities in Southern California, will advise Feinstein on 
education, small business assistance and other issues of importance to those 
communities. 
</P>
<P>
Woo, a Democrat, is the only Asian who has served on the council. He was first 
elected in 1985 and reelected in 1989. 
</P>
