<HEADLINE>
<P>
JENNINGS WILL NOT SEEK REELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William H. Jennings, who has served on the Santa Monica City Council since 
1979, announced Wednesday that he will not seek reelection this fall. 
</P>
<P>
His decision means that two of the three council seats up for election on Nov. 
6 will be open. 
</P>
<P>
Councilwoman Christine Reed will be the only incumbent seeking reelection. 
Councilman David Finkel is stepping down to run for municipal judge in Santa 
Monica. 
</P>
<P>
Jennings, an attorney, said in a prepared statement that he decided not to seek 
a fourth term for family reasons. 
</P>
<P>
"Over the past 12 years, I have devoted a great deal of time to this city, to 
issues of concern to me and to our residents," he said. "Now I would like to 
spend more time at home with my wife and children." 
</P>
<P>
The filing deadline for candidates for City Council is next Wednesday at 5 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
