<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPENING FOR LAVISH POST OFFICE DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The much-anticipated opening of the lavish new Beverly Hills Post Office on 
Maple Drive has been delayed at least until October, postal officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The four-story structure, which will include underground parking, is nearly 
complete, but construction crews apparently underestimated the time it would 
take to finish the final phase of the project. 
</P>
<P>
When the post office is finished, it will become the main postal facility in 
Beverly Hills, replacing the one on Crescent Drive. Postal officials said 
Beverly Hills residents can expect faster mail service once the building is 
completed because city postal workers will move back there from their temporary 
office in West Los Angeles. 
</P>
