<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTSCOPE; 
</P>
<P>
ALL-STAR SOCCER TEAM LOSES TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The West L.A. Shooting Stars soccer team lost the championship game of the 
Hawaii Cup, but didn't come home empty-handed. 
</P>
<P>
The all-star team of 9- and 10-year-old girls won the Governor's Cup, given to 
the team demonstrating the highest level of sportsmanship in the tournament. 
The team also earned the Tournament Director's Award, which includes a waiver 
for the $450 tournament fee for next year's entry. 
</P>
<P>
Goalies Sara Chieffo and Lynne Brinkman did not allow a goal during regulation 
play in the tournament and Elizabeth Bernier scored all but one of the team's 
goals. 
</P>
<P>
The Shooting Stars lost the championship game to Diamond Head (Oahu), 3-2, in a 
shoot-out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
