<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE, FULLERTON SET FIREWORKS VOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Voters in the cities of Orange and Fullerton will decide in November whether to 
prohibit "safe and sane" fireworks. 
</P>
<P>
Councils in both cities this week voted to put the issue on the ballot. 
</P>
<P>
In May, the Orange council passed an interim ordinance banning some fireworks, 
including "Piccolo" or "Whistling Petes" and sparklers, deemed most dangerous 
by the Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
According to a recent Fire Department report, firefighters found no illegal 
fireworks for sale during this year's Fourth of July holiday period but 
confiscated several boxes of the banned items from Orange residents. 
</P>
<P>
Fireworks are illegal in all of the county's unincorporated areas; only six of 
the county's 29 cities allow the sale and use of fireworks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
