<HEADLINE>
<P>
BABY IN CRITICAL CONDITION AFTER NEAR-DROWNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CYPRESS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 14-month-old baby was in critical condition Wednesday after her mother found 
her floating face down in a pool, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Justine Pesicka was taken to Los Alamitos Medical Center, where she was revived 
by doctors and later transferred by helicopter to Long Beach Memorial Hospital 
after the 4:30 p.m. incident, Cypress Police Sgt. Sandy Stanton said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the child and her mother, both of Anaheim, were visiting relatives 
when the child apparently wandered away. 
</P>
<P>
Justine "went to the back yard and managed to climb a nearby ladder to an 
above-ground pool," Stanton said. 
</P>
<P>
The mother told police that the child could have been face down in the water 
for as long as five minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
