Air Rifles Recalled: Crosman Products Inc. is recalling nearly 53,000 of its 
Model 3100 air rifles, which shoot pellets and are used for target practice, 
because they may have a malfunctioning trigger mechanism, the Consumer Product 
Safety Commission said. No reports of accidental discharge have been reported. 
Owners should discontinue use and call (800) 836-3100 for instructions on 
returning the rifles. 
