<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Consulting Firm: Management Resources, a consulting firm that does extensive 
work for expositions and amusement parks, has several new projects in the 
works, including jobs for both Walt Disney Co. and MCA/Universal Studios. 
</P>
<P>
The firm, which just moved to new offices in Tustin, is helping to market 
Disney's Magic Kingdom Club for employees. It also does personnel planning and 
operations for the new Universal Studios attraction in Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the company is doing consulting work for a 1995 World's Fair that 
would be split between Vienna and Budapest. 
</P>
