<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American sprinter Leroy Burrell matched the best performance of the year by 
winning the 100-meter dash in 9.96 seconds at a track and field meet in 
Sestriere, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
Burrell had been trying for a world record, aided by the high altitude. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Johnson ran the 200 meters in 19.88 seconds, the second-fastest 
performance in the world this year. Johnson, who missed the world mark of 19.72 
set by Italy's Pietro Mennea in Mexico City in 1979, said a slow start and a 
bad curve compromised his record chances. 
</P>
