</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. basketball team beat Greece, 103-95, in overtime, in the opening game 
of the qualifying round of the World Championships at Buenos Aires. 
</P>
<P>
The United States, the defending champion, led, 17-6, after five minutes. 
Greece, however, outscored the United States, 50-28, in the next 15 minutes for 
a 56-45 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Today, the United States plays South Korea, which lost to Spain, 130-101. 
</P>
<P>
In another Pool C game, Alexander Volkov had 24 points to lead the Soviet Union 
to a 97-77 victory over Argentina. 
</P>
<P>
In Pool A, Yugoslavia beat Venezuela, 92-84, as Drazen Petrovic had 20 points 
and Vlade Divac 16. 
</P>
