<P>
SATELLITE MIRRORS PLAGUED BY WARPING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mirrors being built for a $747-million series of weather satellites have been 
found to warp and become useless in the temperature extremes of space, a NASA 
official said. The National Aeronautics and Space Administration spokesman said 
that the flaw was discovered by ITT Aerospace, a subcontractor for the project, 
and that the planned weather satellites cannot be completed and launched until 
a solution is found. In another NASA project, a mirror aboard the Hubble Space 
Telescope is producing a blurred image. 
