<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONTALBAN SUES OVER 'FANTASY ISLAND' SHARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Ricardo Montalban filed suit Tuesday against Columbia Pictures, claiming 
that the studio didn't pay him a promised 5% in profits from his "Fantasy 
Island" TV series. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Superior Court suit, seeking $10 million in punitive damages in 
addition to the 5% in profits, claims that the 1977-1983 series earned more 
than $100 million and was one of the most successful in TV history. The suit 
charges that Columbia Pictures Television and Columbia Pictures Industries Inc. 
manipulated accounting practices to avoid paying Montalban a portion of the 
profits generated by the series. 
</P>
<P>
The studio denies that the show ever turned a profit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
