<P>
NO WINNERS FOR LOTTO JACKPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No ticket had all six winning numbers picked Wednesday night in the California 
Lottery's "Lotto 6-53" game, leaving the $31.9-million jackpot unclaimed, 
lottery officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
The jackpot will roll over to an estimated $40 million in Saturday night's 
drawing. 
</P>
<P>
One ticket had five of six numbers plus the bonus number, winning $936,031. 
</P>
<P>
There were 158 tickets with five of six numbers, each earning $5,924. They 
share a prize pool of $936,031. 
</P>
</TEXT>
