<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE GRAB STABBING SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspect in a stabbing was arrested this morning after a three-hour standoff 
with Los Angeles police that ended when tear gas was shot into his North 
Hollywood apartment, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Wilber Weatherly, 47, surrendered about 3:30 a.m. after a special weapons and 
tactics team fired a tear gas canister into a second-floor apartment along the 
11500 block of Magnolia Boulevard, Lt. Stuart Maislin said. 
</P>
<P>
Weatherly, who was treated for exposure to tear gas, was arrested on suspicion 
of assault with a deadly weapon and was being held without bail at County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
Maislin said a man whose identity was not released told officers he had been in 
Weatherly's apartment when Weatherly stabbed him during an argument shortly 
after midnight. The man ran out of the apartment and called for help. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills, where he 
was treated for a superficial chest wound, Maislin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
