today in Schauderville near Indian Ocean city of Port Elizabeth, South Africa, 
and burning tires and debris barricade thoroughfare in the city. Four days of 
rioting in mixed-race townships have left at least 32 people dead, 200 injured 
and stores and schools devastated. Agence France-Presse 
